{
  "doc_id": "56483",
  "text": "Meyerson and Williams [CITATION_1] presented an algorithm for k-anonymity, which guarantees a O(k log(k))-approximation. Aggarwal et al. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] illustrated two ap-proximation algorithms that guarantee a O(k)-approximation solution. Note that although both heuristics and approximation algorithms do not guarantee the minimality of their solution, and we cannot perform any evaluation on the result of a heuristic, an approximation algorithm guarantees near-optimum solutions.",
